to independent fields with their own methodologies, philology found its authority narrowing in scope within newly defined boundaries. Providing a fresh perspective on the evolution of Dutch philology as a discipline in the humanities, this is a fascinating look at a historically vital field of thought.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aLinguistics. 0aPhilology. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aLinguistics. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aBod, Rens, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohannes, Gert-Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKalmthout, Ton, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKok Escalle, Marie-Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagliano-Tromp, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRock, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchlusemann, Rita M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSteyaert, Kris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTollebeek, Jo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZuidervaart, Huib, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZuidervaart, Huib, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 avan Kalmthout, Ton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017z978311060644708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Backlist eBook-Pac